originalText.text: Another one of those physical therapy joints that don't have professionally trained staff.  Any good physical therapy office will review x-rays, MRI and CAT SCAN, and are able to focus on muscle spasms in the areas of pain or discomfort to relieve pain and increase mobility.  Since there are so many offices just trying to bill your insurance I strongly recommend "Hands on Physical Therapy", they have very well trained teams and staff. There's way too many PT offices out there that is solely for the money, you can actually be damaged more from people that don't know what to do or what they are doing.
